When the disc carrier 60 is pulled out of the jacket 10' in the direction indicated by the arrow 76, each tab 45 attached to the top panel 16 of the jacket slips beneath a lip 69 that extends from the upper rim 68 of the carrier 60 at the corners that normally remain within the jacket. This engagement between the carrier 60 and jacket 10' during motion in the outward direction (76) prevents separation of the carrier 60 from the jacket 10' except upon application of transverse forces 78, as described above.
